DAMATURU – The Victims Support Fund (VSF) has today launched the distribution of food items to victims of terrorism in Yobe State. In his opening remarks, the Chairman of the VSF, General TY Danjuma, represented by the Executive Director of VSF, Professor Nana Tanko, said that the distribution is part of the continuing implementation mission of VSF which is to support indigent victims of terrorism and insurgency “has approved support for the distribution of food items to 8,621 households who are recently affected and displaced victims of terrorism in Yobe State. “Approximately, 60,347 individuals would be benefiting from this intervention, the beneficiaries are households affected by the insurgency and in dire need of food assistance. They are currently living as Internally Displaced Persons in formal and informal camps as well as in the host communities in Geidam, Tarmuwa, Damaturu, Gashua and Yunusari Local Government Areas. FCT Council Poll: Abuja Indigenes Commend INEC, Minister For… 17 Roasted In Ogun Tanker Fire Disaster “The intervention involves the distribution of food items estimated to meet the nutritional needs of each households for at least 4 weeks. The detailed package for each benefiting household is made up of 50kg bag consisting of the following Maize flour (15kg), Millet grits, Beans (10kg), Salt (2kg), Vegetable oil (0.75liters×3), Tomato paste (15 sachets), Pepper and Onion paste (15 sachets), Spaghetti and Seasoning cubes- Maggie cubes (2 packs). Yobe State Governor Mai Mala Buni, represented by Dr Abubakar Garba Iliya Commissioner Yobe State Ministry of Humanitarian and Disaster Management, appreciated VSF for the continued support to the IDPs in the state and assured them of continuous cooperation.